CatDescriptText: Mrs. Rosetta McKinney, housewife, 107 Parkhurst Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 31, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the District Attorney's office and the courts are exerting all out efforts in prosecuting equal rights cases in which Negroes are the victims?"  Answer reads: "They just wash their hands of the cases and so therefore, it is a waste of time."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rosetta McKinney, wearing eyeglasses, dark blouse, and light colored coat, posed with arms folded across chest, in front of brick building
